    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-06-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-06-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="16"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d16">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 835.413.W27/7.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-06-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 30, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In celebration of the centenary of Argentine independence, American citizens
                    resident in Buenos Aires will present to the Argentine Nation a noble monument
                    to Washington. On the fourth of July I shall make the presentation in behalf of
                    the American Colony, and the gift will be accepted by President Saenz Peña in
                    person. Not only our fellow-citizens here, but the Argentine Government, the
                    public and the press would highly appreciate a message on that occasion from the
                    President.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
